Title : Arnoud van Doorn
Text : '''Arnoud van Doorn''' (born 18 March 1966, [[The Hague]])<ref>{{nl icon}} [https://pzcindenhaag.wordpress.com/2010/04/12/kandidatenlijst-pvv/ List of PVV candidates, 2010 elections]</ref> is a politician. He was a member of the anti-[[Islam]] party,  [[Party for Freedom|Dutch Freedom Party (PVV)]], before converting to Islam.

==Political career==
Arnoud van Doorn  used to be part of the PVV of [[Geert Wilders]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/shortcuts/2013/oct/23/arnoud-van-doorn-anti-islamic-convert-hajj|title=Arnoud van Doorn: from anti-Islamic film-maker to hajj pilgrim|publisher=[[The Guardian|The Guardian UK]]|date=23 October 2013|accessdate=22 April 2014}}</ref> In December 2011, the party broke with Van Doorn.<ref>{{nl icon}} [http://www.binnenlandsbestuur.nl/bestuur-en-organisatie/nieuws/haagse-pvv-breekt-met-raadslid.3126764.lynkx Haagse PVV breekt met raadslid], Binnenlands Bestuur, 14 December 2011</ref>

He decided to become a Muslim a few months later and announced his conversion to Islam in April 2012. Soon after, he performed [[Hajj]] to Saudi Arabia and visited the [[Prophet's Mosque]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amsterdamherald.com/index.php/rss/722-20130301-from-wilders-to-muhammad-former-freedom-party-vice-chairman-converts-islam-religion-immigration-cultural-integration-the-hague-council-pvv-netherlands-dutch-politics|title=From Wilders to Muhammad: Former Freedom Party vice-chairman converts to Islam|publisher=The Amsterdam Herald|date=1 March 2013|accessdate=22 April 2014}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2013/10/22/arnoud-van-doorn-hajj-conversion_n_4141718.html|title=Former Anti-Islam Film-Maker, Arnoud Van Doorn, Peforms [sic] Hajj After Becoming Muslim|publisher=[[Huffington Post|Huffington Post UK]]|date=22 October 2013|accessdate=22 April 2014}}</ref> He said that the overwhelming reaction of Muslims around the world against the film ''[[Fitna (film)|Fitna]]'' made him interested to learn more; all this led to his decision to convert to Islam.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.saudigazette.com.sa/index.cfm?method=home.regcon&contentid=20130422162428|title="I am sorry, O Prophet..."|publisher=[[Saudi Gazette]]|date=23 April 2013|accessdate=22 April 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140424063331/http://www.saudigazette.com.sa/index.cfm?method=home.regcon&contentid=20130422162428|archive-date=24 April 2014|dead-url=yes}}</ref> He stated, "Right now I am still feeling regret for having distributed the film. I have a responsibility to correct the mistakes that I've done in the past."<ref>http://rahyafte.com/en/3453/member-anti-islamic-party-netherland-converted-islam/</ref>

Later, his eldest son, Iskander Amien De Vries,<ref>{{cite news|author1=MUHAMMAD JAWED|title=Van Doorn's son embraces Islam|url=http://www.arabnews.com/news/560946|accessdate=14 October 2014|work=Arab News|date=25 April 2014}}</ref> followed him in converting to Islam in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arabnews.com/news/560946|title=Van Doorn's son embraces Islam|publisher=Arabnews.com|date=22 April 2014 |accessdate=22 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.khaleejtimes.com/kt-article-display-1.asp?xfile=data/nationgeneral/2014/April/nationgeneral_April148.xml&section=nationgeneral|title=Son of distributor of anti-Islam film accepts Islam|publisher=Khaleejtimes.com|date=21 April 2014 |accessdate=22 April 2014}}</ref>

Until May 2014, he served as a member of [[The Hague]] City Council for the [[:nl:Islam Democraten#Partijbreuk|PvdE]], a political party based on Islam. At the moment he is President of the [[European Dawah Foundation|European Da'wah Foundation]], and Ambassador of Celebrity Relations for the [[Canadian Dawah Association|Canadian Da'wah Association]] in Europe. He is a Member of the Board and Official Representative for the PvdE in the city council of The Hague.<ref>http://rahyafte.com/en/3453/member-anti-islamic-party-netherland-converted-islam/</ref>

In February 2014 Van Doorn was sentenced to pay a fine on leaking secret documents to the press, possession of an illegal flare gun, and for selling soft drugs to minors, in 2014 it was raised to an extra 240 hours of community service. Van Doorn claimed to have sold the soft drugs in order to catch a drug dealer, although the judge called his explanation "very implausable".<ref>{{nl icon}} [http://www.ad.nl/ad/nl/1012/Nederland/article/detail/3597083/2014/02/14/Werkstraf-en-boete-voor-raadslid-Arnoud-van-Doorn.dhtml Werkstraf en boete voor raadslid Arnoud van Doorn], 14 February 2014, [[Algemeen Dagblad]]</ref>

On Monday 6 August 2018,  [[Willie Dille]], a Dutch politician, published a video on Facebook announcing her departure from the city council and alleging Van Doorn had organised a group of Muslims to abduct, rape and abuse her in March 2017, in an effort to silence her criticism of Islam.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.geenstijl.nl/5143286/oh-oke/|title=WTF-video. PVV-raadslid 070 Willie Dille beschuldigt Arnoud van Doorns "Marokkanen" van ontvoering en verkrachting|last='Spartacus'|first=|date=2018-08-08|website=www.geenstijl.nl|language=nl|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-08-09}}</ref>  On Wednesday 8 August 2018 Dille died by suicide after apologizing to her loved ones on Facebook.<ref>https://nos.nl/artikel/2245283-haags-pvv-raadslid-willie-dille-plotseling-overleden.html</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.omroepwest.nl/nieuws/3675849/Haags-PVV-raadslid-Willie-Dille-overleden|title=Haags PVV-raadslid Willie Dille overleden|work=Omroep West|access-date=2018-08-09|language=nl-NL}}</ref>

